	abstract = {In 2008, a survey found that less than 13\% of Wikipedia contributors worldwide were women. The free online encyclopedia that “anyone can edit” was outed as being mostly run by men. A follow up survey in 2011 found similar results: globally, 9\% of contributors were women; in the U.S., it was 15\%. Meanwhile, there appeared to be no significant gender difference in readership rates.

